look, how about this?

08:04.518 --> 08:06.820
How about we give it a month,
and then we'll see
where we're at.

08:06.920 --> 08:09.456
Okay? All right.
Okay. Thanks.

08:09.557 --> 08:11.625
Can I have one of these?
No, you leave that there.

08:11.725 --> 08:15.395
Yeah.
Right up the stairs.
Thanks.

08:15.495 --> 08:18.265
Robert.
How's work going today?

08:18.365 --> 08:21.201
- Uh, fine.
- Yeah?

08:23.136 --> 08:25.873
Yeah, they said you
needed to talk with me?

08:25.973 --> 08:28.642
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Have a seat.
Have a seat.

08:28.742 --> 08:32.980
Ah, busy day.
Busy day here
at Shop and Save.

08:33.080 --> 08:35.115
We got a lot of--

08:35.215 --> 08:37.517
[ Tapping Buttons ]

08:37.618 --> 08:40.821
[ Tapping Continues ]
Fix that later.

08:40.921 --> 08:42.856
Whatever.

08:42.956 --> 08:47.094
Uh, so, Robert,
how's the whole everything?

08:48.829 --> 08:50.030
Fine.

08:52.265 --> 08:54.902
- Yours?
- Great.

08:55.969 --> 08:58.005
In fact, it's great
that you asked,

08:58.105 --> 09:00.007
because...

09:01.308 --> 09:03.143
I have something
you need to see.

09:03.243 --> 09:06.479
Now, I think
I found something that
could really help us all out.

09:06.580 --> 09:08.515
I don't wanna
hype it up too much.

09:08.616 --> 09:10.517
I'm just gonna cut
to the chase here. Okay?

09:10.618 --> 09:13.587
Okay.
I truly think
that this...

09:13.687 --> 09:17.190
could change
the way we celebrate
the holiday season.

09:17.290 --> 09:19.026
Are you ready?

09:21.161 --> 09:23.396
Are you ready, sir?

09:23.496 --> 09:25.699
Uh, yeah.
Yeah? Okay.

09:26.667 --> 09:29.603
These are...

09:33.140 --> 09:34.975
Christmas recipe books,

09:35.075 --> 09:39.112
stuffed full
of holiday-themed
dinners and desserts--

09:39.212 --> 09:42.683
everything
from St. Nick Stew
to my personal favorite,

09:42.783 --> 09:45.085
Christmas tree-shaped cookies--
all delicious.

09:45.185 --> 09:47.454
I've made
many of them myself.
Really?

09:47.554 --> 09:50.423
Y-You m-made them yourself?

09:50.523 --> 09:53.460
No. It's--
It's part of the pitch.

09:53.560 --> 09:56.730
Oh.
Look, Robert, I'm not
trying to sell you this thing.

09:56.830 --> 09:59.132
I want us to go
into business together,
you and me.

10:01.034 --> 10:03.336
- I don't understand.
- Okay.

10:05.072 --> 10:09.643
Look, all I have to do
is get a team of people
working under me,

10:09.743 --> 10:12.746
and then they get a team
of people working under them,

10:12.846 --> 10:15.015
and then we
all start profiting
off of each other.

10:15.115 --> 10:19.019
See, the more people
we get involved,
the more money we make.

10:20.353 --> 10:24.992
There's no chance
we can fail
if we never give up.

10:25.092 --> 10:27.861
Well, yeah,
that makes sense to me.

10:27.961 --> 10:30.230
Yes. Yes. Okay.
So, what do you think?

10:30.330 --> 10:33.066
Should we get everyone
up in the store
selling these things? Huh?

10:33.166 --> 10:35.368
