This is a bad idea.

24:21.227 --> 24:23.496
All right, Alex,
thank you very much.
I've heard enough.

24:23.596 --> 24:25.164
I'm gonna do it.

24:25.264 --> 24:29.301
[ Man ]
* The dream alive

24:29.401 --> 24:33.172
- Mom!
- I'm going out on a date!
That's all I'm doing!

24:33.272 --> 24:35.307
Would you please just relax?

24:35.407 --> 24:38.177
Who knows? Maybe we
won't even get along.

24:42.348 --> 24:44.350
* Shadows

24:44.450 --> 24:48.688
* On the mistletoe

24:49.656 --> 24:53.059
* No one to kiss you

24:53.159 --> 24:56.395
* You're alone

24:56.495 --> 25:00.232
* I'm looking at your gift

25:00.332 --> 25:04.036
* I wonder where you are

25:04.136 --> 25:07.874
* On someone's arm

25:11.177 --> 25:13.946
* I'm dry

25:14.046 --> 25:16.649
* And warm

25:16.749 --> 25:20.953
* I face the fire

25:21.053 --> 25:24.256
[ Doorbell Rings ]
* My hands are cold

25:26.325 --> 25:29.528
Hi.
Hello.

25:29.629 --> 25:31.631
Are you ready?

25:31.731 --> 25:35.434
Yes. I-I do--
I-I have directions.

25:35.534 --> 25:38.437
Oh! Okay.

25:38.537 --> 25:41.608
Take me away.
Okay.

25:51.383 --> 25:53.319
Thank you.

25:56.589 --> 25:58.524
What did you--
What did you order again?

25:58.625 --> 26:01.093
It's like a salad.

26:02.328 --> 26:05.131
That's a... great choice.

26:05.231 --> 26:07.566
Mm, thanks.

26:09.435 --> 26:13.339
You-- You look
very nice tonight.

26:13.439 --> 26:16.008
Oh. Thank you.

26:16.108 --> 26:19.879
And... your shoes look
very nice too.

26:19.979 --> 26:22.982
Oh! Thank you again.
I-- I--

26:23.082 --> 26:27.186
I just mean that you--
you look very nice,
that's what I--

26:30.657 --> 26:34.393
So, you had to go
to the restroom?
No, I'm okay.

26:34.493 --> 26:36.595
No, no.
I meant your car.

26:36.696 --> 26:40.733
You said you had to go
to the restroom and that's
why it was stuck in the garage.

26:41.600 --> 26:44.203
Yeah. Right.

26:44.303 --> 26:46.305
So, what happened?

26:46.405 --> 26:49.876
Oh. I--

26:49.976 --> 26:52.311
I was backing the car
out of the garage,

26:52.411 --> 26:55.682
and I closed
the garage door,
and then I had to go.

27:05.057 --> 27:08.494
Something like that
almost happened to me once.

27:08.594 --> 27:11.097
Really?
No.

27:11.197 --> 27:14.333
[ Laughs ]
Don't feel bad.
[ Laughs ]

27:20.907 --> 27:23.509
How does your food taste?

27:23.609 --> 27:26.312
Oh, it's-- it's fine.

27:26.412 --> 27:28.948
You don't like it, do you?

27:29.048 --> 27:32.752
Well, to be honest,
I think it could
taste better.

27:32.852 --> 27:37.389
I mean, I think it looks nice,
but I think it could
taste better, I think.

27:37.489 --> 27:39.959
Mine's horrible.

27:40.059 --> 27:41.928
[ Chuckles ]

27:42.028 --> 27:43.930
And this is coming
from somebody
who eats TV dinners.

27:44.030 --> 27:46.866
I love TV dinners.
Yes.

27:49.635 --> 27:52.171
Okay.

27:52.271 --> 27:54.006
I've seen you before.

27:54.106 --> 27:58.410
Where?
When I go shopping.

27:58.510 --> 28:01.180
You mean at--
at the store?

28:01.280 --> 28:05.517
Yeah. Every day you eat
and you sketch pictures.

28:05.617 --> 28:10.122
And I snuck a peek,
and I think
they're really good.

28:10.222 --> 28:13.960
You've been watching me?
I think you're
a real artist.

28:14.060 --> 28:16.428
Oh.

28:18.164 --> 28:21.467
Good one.
No, no, no. It's true.

28:24.670 --> 28:26.873
Well, thank you.

28:33.345 --> 28:35.214
When I was a little girl,

28:35.314 --> 28:38.417
my favorite book to read
was Grimm's Fairy Tales.

28:38.517 --> 28:41.087
Oh, I wanted life
to be like that.

28:41.187 --> 28:45.257
You know, find true love
and live happily ever after.

28:45.357 --> 28:48.761
You know, all the dreams
we have growing up.

28:50.496 --> 28:54.500
And then...
everything changes.

28:55.902 --> 28:59.438
You know, every year
that goes by just--

29:03.810 --> 29:06.946
It'll all be okay.

29:10.549 --> 29:13.385
There's no chance
to fail...

29:13.485 --> 29:15.788
if you don't give up.

29:17.824 --> 29:20.126
Oh!
[ Chuckles ]

29:20.226 --> 29:22.461
Let's make each other
a promise, okay?

29:22.561 --> 29:25.798
A promise?
A-A-A promise of what?

29:25.898 --> 29:28.700
That we'll never give up.

29:28.801 --> 29:30.937
Okay.

29:34.673 --> 29:37.376
[ Both Laughing ]

29:42.148 --> 29:44.984
So, how do you like working
at the grocery store?

29:45.084 --> 29:48.354
Oh, it's fine.
It's fine, you know.

29:48.454 --> 29:51.123
There's more to it
than meets the eye, you know.
Oh, I'm sure.

29:51.223 --> 29:53.225
Yeah.

29:53.325 --> 29:57.396
You go on dates often?
This is my first one
since my husband left.

29:57.496 --> 29:58.564
Oh.

29:58.664 --> 30:00.732
[ Man ]
Hop on in.

30:00.833 --> 30:05.104
Oh, thank you.
Hey, do-- do
I pay you now or--

30:05.204 --> 30:08.774
You can pay me
after the ride.
Okay. Thank you.

30:08.875 --> 30:11.944
[ Mary ]
Get in all right?
Yeah.

30:12.044 --> 30:14.013
** [ Marching Band: "Hark!
The Herald Angels Sing" ]

30:14.113 --> 30:16.415
Do you think
it's safe?
Oh, of course it's safe.

30:16.515 --> 30:18.084
No, it's safe.
Yeah?

30:18.184 --> 30:19.518
Mm-hmm.

30:21.120 --> 30:23.789
Here. Yeah.
Oh. Thank you.

30:23.890 --> 30:26.558
You're welcome.
[ Man ]
Merry Christmas!

30:28.694 --> 30:31.463
Oh, I'm really
enjoying this.

30:31.563 --> 30:34.133
The lights are so pretty.

30:34.233 --> 30:37.369
They are, aren't they?
Yeah.

30:37.469 --> 30:41.073
[ Church Bells Tolling ]

30:41.173 --> 30:43.809
It's getting kind
of cold though.

30:43.910 --> 30:48.280
Yeah. I wish they had
another blanket.

30:48.380 --> 30:50.549
I've got an idea.

30:50.649 --> 30:53.819
Why don't we both use
this one?

30:53.920 --> 30:55.854
Okay.
[ Laughs ]

30:55.955 --> 30:58.590
That's good.

30:58.690 --> 31:00.559
Oh, there.

31:02.228 --> 31:04.196
Thank you.
You're welcome.

31:04.296 --> 31:06.198
[ Mary ]
I think I've
finally gotten warm.

31:06.298 --> 31:10.269
You're okay now?
I'm fine, yes.

31:10.369 --> 31:12.771
I had
a good time tonight.
Oh, me too.

31:12.871 --> 31:15.741
Yeah?
Yeah.

31:15.841 --> 31:19.845
Okay.
Okay. Yeah.

31:19.946 --> 31:24.283
** [ Carolers Singing
"O Holy Night" ]

31:31.757 --> 31:34.526
What's that?

31:34.626 --> 31:37.829
Um, it sounds
like singing.

31:37.930 --> 31:40.466
Oh. Well.

31:41.567 --> 31:44.370
[ Sighs ]

31:44.470 --> 31:48.240
** [ Continues ]

31:58.517 --> 32:02.421
Oh. It's beautiful.

32:02.521 --> 32:04.456
Yes, it is.

32:07.759 --> 32:10.062
* Fall

32:10.162 --> 32:15.401
* On your knees

32:15.501 --> 32:18.404
* Oh, hear

32:18.504 --> 32:22.374
* The angel voices

32:22.474 --> 32:24.310
So,

32:24.410 --> 32:27.546
how was our first date?
* O night

32:27.646 --> 32:30.983
* Divine

32:31.083 --> 32:33.052
* O night

32:33.152 --> 32:36.255
It--
* When Christ was born

32:36.355 --> 32:38.257
It--

32:38.357 --> 32:41.127
Was wonderful?
It was... wonderful.

32:41.227 --> 32:43.295
[ Laughs ]
Wonderful.

32:43.395 --> 32:47.233
* Divine

32:47.333 --> 32:50.469
* O night
I wish it would...

32:50.569 --> 32:52.738
go on for more.

32:52.838 --> 32:58.710
Well, we're gonna see
each other tomorrow.
* O night divine *

32:58.810 --> 33:00.746
Good.

33:07.053 --> 33:08.587
Good night!

33:10.822 --> 33:12.724
Good night!

33:43.889 --> 33:45.791
You happy, Mom?

33:46.858 --> 33:48.794
I'm so happy.

33:51.763 --> 33:53.932
I'm sorry about before.

33:54.032 --> 33:56.068
I just wanna protect you.

33:56.168 --> 33:58.504
I know, honey.

33:58.604 --> 34:00.372
That's all right.

34:00.472 --> 34:02.774
This is the right thing.
It really is.

34:02.874 --> 34:04.776
You have to trust me.

34:05.877 --> 34:08.480
Okay.

34:08.580 --> 34:10.949
I trust you.

34:11.049 --> 34:13.018
That's my girl.

34:13.119 --> 34:16.487
I love you, Mom.
I love you too, honey.

34:19.324 --> 34:21.659
[ Kisses ]
Good night.

34:22.893 --> 34:24.763
I'm glad you had fun.

34:28.734 --> 34:31.803
[ Clock Ticking ]

34:50.922 --> 34:52.924
[ Exhales ]

34:53.024 --> 34:56.428
[ Clock Ticking ]

35:30.095 --> 35:33.098
[ Woman ]
* Making spirits bright

35:33.199 --> 35:36.268
* What fun it is
to ride and sing
a sleighing song tonight *

35:36.368 --> 35:38.737
[ Gasps ]
* Jingle bells

35:38.837 --> 35:41.340
* Ji-Jingle bells

35:41.440 --> 35:43.542
* Jingle all the way

35:43.642 --> 35:45.677
[ Hits Radio Button ]
** [ Stops ]

35:48.580 --> 35:50.216
[ Exhales ]

35:52.851 --> 35:55.721
[ Beeps ]
[ Dial Tone ]

36:00.426 --> 36:02.928
[ Dial Tone ]
[ Beeps ]

36:11.203 --> 36:13.272
[ Beeps ]
[ Dial Tone ]

36:16.975 --> 36:20.011
[ TV: Man Speaking,
Indistinct ]

36:20.111 --> 36:21.980
And here's the question.
Yes, I'm ready.

36:22.080 --> 36:23.715
[ Doorbell Rings ]

36:25.150 --> 36:28.119
Hello, sir.
My name is
Damien Montgomery.

36:28.220 --> 36:32.291
I was curious if you'd be
interested in buying sleds
to keep kids off the streets.

36:32.391 --> 36:34.593
- Well, how much?
- Five dollars.

36:34.693 --> 36:37.195
Oh. Uh--

36:39.398 --> 36:41.867
- Did the phone just ring?
- No.

36:41.967 --> 36:44.903
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

36:45.003 --> 36:49.841
- Oh. So, how much--
how much are they?
- Five dollars.

36:52.411 --> 36:56.014
All-- All right.
I'll, uh--
I'll take a sled.

36:56.114 --> 36:59.985
Man, is that all you're
going to spend to help keep
the kids off the streets?

37:00.085 --> 37:01.920
[ Phone Rings ]
Well, I'll-- Oh.

37:03.355 --> 37:06.258
[ Ringing ]
Wait.

37:06.358 --> 37:08.960
[ Ringing ]
Don't hang up.
Wait, wait, wait.

37:09.060 --> 37:11.430
Don't hang up.
[ Ringing ]

37:11.530 --> 37:15.467
Hello. Mary?
[ Voice Mumbling ]

37:16.902 --> 37:21.440
No. No, I'm perfectly happy
with my phone service.

37:21.540 --> 37:24.042
[ Mumbling Continues ]

37:24.142 --> 37:26.745
Look-- Look-- Look,
don't-- don't-- What?

37:26.845 --> 37:30.081
[ Mumbling Continues ]
[ Doorbell Rings ]

37:30.181 --> 37:31.950
Good-bye.
[ Handset Slams Down In Cradle ]

37:32.050 --> 37:33.785
Damn it!

37:33.885 --> 37:35.387
Yes? Oh.

37:35.487 --> 37:38.357
Hi.
Oh, Mary.

37:38.457 --> 37:41.960
So, why didn't you call?
Oh, I was just about to.

37:42.060 --> 37:44.162
Oh.

37:44.262 --> 37:47.966
So, did you, uh, plan
any things for today fun?

37:48.066 --> 37:50.336
Fun?

37:51.236 --> 37:53.305
What are those?

37:55.341 --> 37:58.043
** [ Woman Singing
"Ave Maria" ]

38:09.421 --> 38:12.123
** [ Mary Humming ]

38:12.223 --> 38:14.393
Hey, wait for me.
Oh, sorry.

38:14.493 --> 38:17.596
[ Both Laugh ]
** [ Humming Continues ]

38:17.696 --> 38:21.467
I haven't come here
since I was a kid.
It's great.

38:21.567 --> 38:24.770
Yeah, we used
to come and cut down
our Christmas trees here.

38:24.870 --> 38:28.407
But I don't think they
let you do that anymore.
Oh, I'm sure they don't.

38:28.507 --> 38:30.609
Oh, I wanted
to ask you a question.
Yeah?

38:30.709 --> 38:33.379
I would just love it
if you would be my date...

38:33.479 --> 38:35.747
for this party
on Christmas Eve.

38:37.349 --> 38:39.351
I'd love to.
You would?

38:39.451 --> 38:42.253
Of course I'll--
I'll go. Sure.

38:42.354 --> 38:44.956
Really?
Yeah. Why wouldn't I?

38:45.056 --> 38:47.893
Well, I don't know
how to answer that.
[ Both Laugh ]

38:47.993 --> 38:49.961
Hey.

38:52.798 --> 38:55.734
** [ "Ave Maria" Continues ]

39:01.206 --> 39:03.108
It's so beautiful...

39:05.310 --> 39:09.347
if we just slow down enough
to really see it.

39:10.416 --> 39:13.051
I've never seen it before.

39:19.391 --> 39:21.527
I may--

39:23.161 --> 39:25.163
I may have wasted
my whole life.

39:25.263 --> 39:28.667
Robert, stop it.
You haven't.

39:30.469 --> 39:34.339
- I have.
- No, you didn't.

39:34.440 --> 39:36.842
Don't think about the past.

39:36.942 --> 39:39.778
The past is just...

39:39.878 --> 39:42.548
something we can't do
anything about.

39:44.349 --> 39:48.920
And the future is--
Who knows?
It could be wonderful or...

39:50.456 --> 39:53.959
[ Sighs ]
it could be something else.

39:54.059 --> 39:55.994
We don't know.

39:56.094 --> 39:58.864
So...

39:58.964 --> 40:01.467
let's just be happy now.

40:03.502 --> 40:05.737
All right.

40:05.837 --> 40:10.542
Let's just care about
right now.

40:11.743 --> 40:14.446
I can't wait to give you
your Christmas present.

40:16.582 --> 40:19.117
My Christmas present?
Yeah.

40:19.217 --> 40:21.152
It's perfect.

40:21.252 --> 40:23.221
Oh. Good.

40:23.321 --> 40:25.256
You wanna go down again?

40:25.356 --> 40:27.559
Yeah.
Come on.

40:31.229 --> 40:33.799
- You comin'?
- [ Gasping ]

40:33.899 --> 40:38.537
** [ "Ave Maria" Continues ]

40:38.637 --> 40:41.006
[ Hits Radio Button ]
** [ Stops ]

40:44.075 --> 40:46.044
Mike?

40:49.715 --> 40:51.983
[ Woman ]
* Jingle bells

40:52.083 --> 40:54.319
[ Car Alarm Chirps ]
So, what are we
gonna get her?

40:54.419 --> 40:57.923
* Jingle all the way
I wanna get her
the perfect gift.

40:58.023 --> 41:00.759
* Oh, what fun it is to ride
Uh-huh. And what is that?

41:00.859 --> 41:05.363
It's the perfect gift.
Ah. Can you be
a little more specific?

41:05.463 --> 41:07.465
Well, I don't know
what it is yet,

41:07.566 --> 41:12.571
but I will know
what it is when I see it.
Okay.

41:12.671 --> 41:15.373
- Jeans? Is she
a jean wearer?
- No, no, no.

41:15.473 --> 41:17.275
All right, well,
we'll figure it out.

41:17.375 --> 41:20.311
Are you seeing anything
that kind of resembles
the perfect gift?

41:20.411 --> 41:22.714
Here. How about that?
That looks good.

41:22.814 --> 41:25.951
I don't know about that.
Are those the right sizes?

41:26.051 --> 41:27.318
Uh, yeah. Probably.

41:27.418 --> 41:30.789
Robert, look at this.
Hey! Hey!
What? A lot of stuff here.

41:30.889 --> 41:32.958
What do you say?
Oh, okay.

41:33.058 --> 41:37.328
This is something else.
I-- I would wear this.
I wouldn't.

41:37.428 --> 41:40.131
No. No.

41:40.231 --> 41:42.668
Ah. Here we go.
Give her this.
She'll like it.

41:42.768 --> 41:44.870
Really?
Yeah. Trust me.

41:44.970 --> 41:46.872
Maybe that's
the perfect one.
We don't know right now.

41:46.972 --> 41:49.641
Maybe later on
we will know.
I don't like that color.

41:49.741 --> 41:53.411
See, this is progress.
We're figuring stuff out.
I'm not sure she'll like that.

41:53.511 --> 41:56.114
[ Laughs ]
Cute, right?

41:56.214 --> 42:00.218
Yeah. They're adorable,
if you're shopping
for a five-year-old.

42:00.318 --> 42:01.820
God, you're lucky
you brought me.

42:01.920 --> 42:04.823
* Jingle bells, jingle bells
Jingle all the way *

42:04.923 --> 42:07.158
- * Oh, what fun it is to ride
- What's going on?

42:07.258 --> 42:08.594
* In a one-horse open sleigh

42:08.694 --> 42:12.631
This is it.
This is the gift.

42:12.731 --> 42:15.801
Okay. Well, what
about all this stuff?

42:17.268 --> 42:20.972
Well-- Well, that's all
I need, you know, but--

42:21.072 --> 42:24.142
Okay.
Just in case, we better get
this stuff too.

42:24.242 --> 42:26.077
Okay.
* Jingle bells

42:26.177 --> 42:28.179
Thanks, Mike.
I really appreciate it.
Yeah.

42:28.279 --> 42:31.082
All right. That was fun.
That was great. Thank you.

42:31.182 --> 42:33.685
I'll see you in the morning.
Okay. Have a good night.

42:33.785 --> 42:35.887
Yeah, you too, Robert.

42:41.793 --> 42:44.462
Hey, uh, Robert.
Hey, Robert.

42:44.562 --> 42:47.633
Hi. I'm Alex,
Mary's daughter.

42:47.733 --> 42:51.402
Oh. Hello.
Hi.

42:51.502 --> 42:53.404
So, what have you got there?

42:53.504 --> 42:55.073
Presents.

42:55.173 --> 42:56.708
For me?

42:56.808 --> 42:59.778
Uh, no.
[ Chuckles ]

42:59.878 --> 43:02.047
No. I know. I'm kidding.

43:02.147 --> 43:03.581
Yeah.

43:03.682 --> 43:05.550
It's freezing, huh?

43:05.651 --> 43:07.452
Maybe you should
go back inside.

43:07.552 --> 43:11.156
- I don't want you
to catch cold or anything.
- All right.

43:11.256 --> 43:13.792
Um, I just wanted
to say, Robert,
if you ever need anything,

43:13.892 --> 43:16.728
anything at all, you just
come on over and ask.

43:16.828 --> 43:19.898
I'm happy to help.
Oh, that's very nice of you.
Thank you.

43:19.998 --> 43:21.499
All right.
Nice meeting you.

43:21.599 --> 43:22.801
And you. Okay.
Okay.

43:22.901 --> 43:24.636
Good night.
Night.

43:24.736 --> 43:26.304
Hey, Robert?

43:28.539 --> 43:31.042
My mom,
she really likes you.

43:32.310 --> 43:35.346
You make her happy,
which makes me happy.

43:36.648 --> 43:38.750
Good night.
Good night.

44:07.679 --> 44:09.748
[ Sighs ]

44:14.953 --> 44:17.055
[ Beeps ]
[ Dial Tone ]

44:19.090 --> 44:24.295
- [ Beeping ]
- [ Busy Signal ]

44:24.395 --> 44:26.264
[ Busy Signal ]

44:28.033 --> 44:30.836
[ Beeps ]
[ Handset Settles In Cradle ]

44:40.812 --> 44:44.082
[ Loud Beeping ]

44:47.252 --> 44:49.220
Hello.

44:49.320 --> 44:51.489
- Mary?
- Hi.

44:51.589 --> 44:53.725
Hello.

44:53.825 --> 44:57.128
[ Sighs ]
I missed you today.

44:57.228 --> 44:59.197
Missed me?

44:59.297 --> 45:03.068
- Hmm, yeah.
- Well, I missed you too.

45:04.770 --> 45:08.774
Okay. I just called
to say that...

45:10.141 --> 45:13.411
and to ask
if you wanna, um,

45:13.511 --> 45:17.382
spend the day
with me tomorrow.
What, the whole day?

45:17.482 --> 45:20.886
[ Laughs ]
What do you think?

45:20.986 --> 45:24.122
You can take
a day off of work.

45:25.590 --> 45:29.060
Okay. I mean,
that sounds lovely.

45:29.160 --> 45:31.062
Great.

45:32.764 --> 45:36.134
Well, I guess I'll
see you tomorrow morning then.

45:36.234 --> 45:38.036
Yes.

45:39.838 --> 45:42.841
- [ Handset Settles In Cradle ]
- [ Beeps ]

45:44.009 --> 45:46.211
[ Handset Settles In Cradle ]

45:49.881 --> 45:53.785
[ Clock Ticking ]

45:55.620 --> 45:57.488
